					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Adam Morgan</h4>
												<p>Adam Morgan is a culture journalist and critic who lives near Chapel Hill, North Carolina. His writing regularly appears in <em>Esquire</em>, and has also been published in <em>The Paris Review</em>, <em>Scientific American</em>, <em>Los Angeles Times</em>, <em>The Guardian</em>, and more. He spent a decade in Chicago, during which time he founded the <em>Chicago Review of Books</em> and covered the city’s arts and culture for <em>Chicago</em> magazine and the <em>Chicago Reader</em>.</p>
					</div>
